  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct intended for use in adult lumbar spinal fusion procedures. The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed; one factor (Test conditions) falls below required level due to single test condition coverage. The intended patient population is skeletally mature adults undergoing posterior lumbar interbody fusion; loading scenario is static compression-bending per ASTM F1717 at 5 mm/min crosshead displacement. Model outputs (construct stiffness, yield load, failure load) are compared to experimental benchmarks. Acceptance is conditional on engineering judgment that single-condition shortfall does not invalidate the overall credibility determination for the regulatory submission context.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/nagaraja-f1717-compression-bending-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/nagaraja-fea-f1717-noncannulated-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/nagaraja-pedicle-screw-fea-ensemble-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-experimental-n11-lab1",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-f1717-experimental-n11-lab2"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-f1717-result-stiffness",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness prediction vs. experimental mean — within 8% across N=11 specimens"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/nagaraja-f1717-result-yield-load",
